  "texts": [
    "• Readability/Enjoyability: Which text sample is easier to read overall?",
    "The annotators also provide detailed justifications for their choices in each aspect of their judgments (see Figure 7).",
    "Table 6: Win rate of Suri-I-ORPO over Suri-SFT in terms of coherence, enjoyability, and informativeness.",
    "Human annotators consistently prefer Suri-I-ORPO to Suri-SFT for about 60-70% of the time across all three categories: coherence, informativeness, and enjoyability.",
    "Annotators note that Suri-SFT often suffers from repetitive ideas, confusing plot points, and a lack of proper conclusions."
